SECTION 1 — DEFINITIONS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

"Software" means the AutoBot source code, compiled binaries, configuration
files, Ansible playbooks, shell scripts, frontend assets, backend services,
AI agent frameworks, documentation, and any other files included in or
distributed alongside this repository, in whole or in part, in original or
modified form.

"You" (or "Your") means any individual, organization, company, or legal
entity obtaining or using the Software in any way.

"Derivative Work" means any work that is based on or derived from the
Software, including modifications, adaptations, translations, ports,
extensions, wrappers, or works that incorporate a substantial portion of
the Software.

"Profit" means any net monetary gain — revenue minus directly associated
operating costs — derived from a product, service, offering, or activity
in which the Software or a Derivative Work plays a material role. This
includes, without limitation:

  - Net revenue from subscriptions, licenses, or sales of a product or
    service built using the Software;
  - Net fees received for consulting, integration, deployment, or managed
    services delivered using the Software;
  - Net advertising, sponsorship, or affiliate revenue generated through a
    platform that materially relies on the Software;
  - Net proceeds from licensing or sublicensing a Derivative Work;
  - Any other net financial gain in which the Software is a meaningful
    contributing factor.

  "Profit" does NOT include:
  - Gross revenue before deduction of reasonable, documented operating costs
    directly attributable to delivering the product or service;
  - Grants, scholarships, or non-profit funding for research or education;
  - Internal productivity gains or cost savings within a non-profit entity;
  - Pre-profit development, prototyping, or testing activity, regardless of
    future commercial intent;
  - Incidental, one-off, or de minimis revenue below a threshold of
    USD $1,000 in a calendar year.

"Copyright Holder" means mrveiss, the sole author and owner of all AutoBot
intellectual property.



