SECTION 2 — UNRESTRICTED GRANT OF RIGHTS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Subject to the profit-sharing obligation in Section 3 and the attribution
requirement in Section 4, the Copyright Holder grants You a worldwide,
perpetual, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to do anything with the
Software, including but not limited to:

  a) Use the Software for any purpose — personal, academic, research,
     internal, commercial, or otherwise;
  b) Copy and reproduce the Software, in whole or in part;
  c) Modify, adapt, extend, and create Derivative Works;
  d) Merge the Software into other projects, products, or systems;
  e) Publish, distribute, sublicense, and share the Software or Derivative
     Works, in source or binary form, to any party;
  f) Build and sell products and services that incorporate the Software;
  g) Use the Software to compete directly with the original project.

No prior permission is required. No fee is due upfront. No use case is
forbidden. The only condition is Section 3: if you profit, you share.


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
SECTION 3 — SUPPORTING DEVELOPMENT
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

If You generate Profit from any product, service, or activity in which the
Software plays a material role, we ask that You consider contributing back
to the project to support its continued development.

This is not a royalty, a tax, or a fee. It is an appeal to fairness from one
builder to another.

3.1 — YOU DECIDE HOW MUCH

The amount, form, and frequency of Your contribution is entirely Your choice.
You know your business and your situation better than anyone. Consider:

  - How central the Software is to what you built;
  - How much Profit you are generating because of it;
  - What you can reasonably afford to give back.

Contributions can take any form that genuinely helps the project:

  a) Financial: Any amount you consider fair, paid to the Copyright Holder
     or via the project's designated contribution channels;

  b) Code: Bug fixes, features, improvements, documentation, or tests
     submitted as pull requests to https://github.com/mrveiss/AutoBot-AI;

  c) Other: Infrastructure, promotion, tooling, mentorship, or any other
     support that helps sustain and grow the project.

No minimum. No ceiling. No approval needed. Just act honestly.

3.2 — WHEN THIS APPLIES

This ask applies once Your cumulative annual Profit attributable to the
Software exceeds USD $5,000 in a calendar year. Below that threshold, no
contribution is expected — go build freely.

Contributions are most meaningful when ongoing, reflecting a continuing
benefit rather than a one-time acknowledgment.

3.3 — LET US KNOW

If you are using the Software to build something profitable, we would love
to hear about it. Reach out via https://github.com/mrveiss/AutoBot-AI — not
because you are required to, but because it helps the maintainer understand
how the Software is being used, recognize contributors, and prioritize future
development.

3.4 — GOOD FAITH AND CONTINUITY

The only thing asked of you is honesty. If this Software helped you succeed,
do something — however small — to help it keep going.

By supporting the project, you directly ensure AutoBot's continuity. Open
software does not sustain itself. It requires ongoing work, maintenance,
and investment. Users who profit from AutoBot and choose to contribute back
are the reason the project can keep growing — and the reason it will still
be here, free and open, for the next person who needs it.

The project depends on the goodwill of those who benefit from it. Deliberately
and indefinitely profiting from the Software with no intent whatsoever to
contribute anything back is contrary to the spirit of this license. In such
cases, the Copyright Holder reserves the right to revoke the rights granted
under Section 2.


